<F P=100> MEXICO </F>
<H3> <TI>   PRI's Zedillo Condemns Guadalajara Bomb </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    PRI's Zedillo Condemns Guadalajara Bomb </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA1106225594 Mexico City XEW Television Network in Spanish 
2041 GMT 11 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1106225594 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City XEW Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Mr. Ernesto Zedillo, Mexican presidential 
candidate for the Institutional Revolutionary Party [PRI], 
speaking before the Mexican medical community, condemned the 
Guadalajara, Jalisco State car bomb attack. 
  [Begin Zedillo recording] Anonymous violence is one of the 
most brutal criminal actions; it attacks Mexican society's most 
appreciated values and must be strongly rejected. We demand 
that the circumstances regarding this crime be clarified and 
that those responsible receive harsh punishment. We Mexicans 
want to live safely, with tranquillity, and with unity. 
Criminal forces must not be allowed to disturb our country's 
social peace. [end recording] 
  The PRI candidate sent a message of solidarity to the people 
of Guadalajara: 
  [Begin Zedillo recording] Once again, Guadalajara and all 
Jalisco residents suffer events that have absolutely nothing to 
do with these civic-minded and hard-working people. We join 
them in their demands for justice. [end recording] [passage 
omitted] 

</TEXT>

