<F P=100> MEXICO </F>
<H3> <TI>   Mexicali Industrial Zone Seeks Taiwan Investment </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Mexicali Industrial Zone Seeks Taiwan Investment </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1106133094 Taipei CNA in English 1300 GMT 11 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1106133094 </F>
<F P=104>  Taipei CNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By Danielle Yang] </F>
  [Text] Taipei, June 11 (CNA) -- The Mexicali industrial 
zone, situated at the border of the United States and Mexico, 
wants more Taiwan investment, a representative of the zone said 
Saturday [11 June]. 
  Investors will be allowed easier access to the North 
American 
Free Trade Area (NAFTA) [as received] after setting up plants 
there, Chuang Chih-lung, an overseas Chinese authorized by the 
zone to court Taiwan investment, said Saturday. 
  Chuang made the call for more Taiwan investment in the wake 
of Republic of China Premier Lien Chan's visit to Mexico last 
week. The only Taiwan companies currently operating in the 
industrial zone are computer makers, Chuang said. 
  Most of the investors in the zone, which encompasses a 
population of a million people, come from the United States, 
Japan, and Taiwan, Chuang noted. He said the low cost of rent 
in the zone and the cheap and abundant labor force there make it 
an ideal place for Taiwan investors wanting to break into the 
North American market. 

</TEXT>

