<F P=102>   PA1306172094 Mexico City NOTIMEX in Spanish 1643 GMT 13 Jun 
94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1306172094 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City NOTIMEX </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Havana, 13 Jun (NOTIMEX) -- Today, the Cuban Foreign 
Ministry confirmed a group of people's forceful entry into the 
German Embassy in Havana and described the action as an "obvious 
provocation." 
  Miguel Alfonso, official spokesman of the Cuban Foreign 
Ministry, has told NOTIMEX: "We want to point out that this 
action has taken place on the very day the president of Mexico 
arrives in Havana and on the eve of the 4th Ibero-American 
summit." 
  The spokesman said the forceful entry of these people into 
the German Embassy "is additional evidence of the harmful 
results of the U.S. policy" of denying visas to those who 
request visas at the U.S. Interests Office here. 

</TEXT>

