<F P=100> Paraguay </F>
<H3> <TI>   Wasmosy Leaves for Ibero-American Summit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Wasmosy Leaves for Ibero-American Summit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY1306220594 Asuncion ULTIMA HORA in Spanish 13 Jun 94 p 13 </F>
<F P=103> PY1306220594 </F>
<F P=104>  Asuncion ULTIMA HORA </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] As of 14 June, President Juan Carlos Wasmosy 
will make his debut in Ibero-American summits. The chief 
executive traveled today to Cartagena, Colombia, where he will 
ask for the other nations' support for the nascent Paraguayan 
democracy. Even though Paraguay has no diplomatic ties with 
Cuba, the chief executive said he would meet with Fidel Castro. 
  Paraguayan President Juan Carlos Wasmosy left this morning 
for the summit of presidents and heads of state of 
Ibero-American countries scheduled in Cartagena, Colombia. This 
will be the fourth Ibero-American summit. Former President 
Andres Rodriguez represented our country in the three previous 
Ibero-American summits which were held in Guadalajara, Mexico; 
Madrid, Spain; and Salvador de Bahia, Brazil. [passage omitted] 
  Foreign Minister Luis Maria Ramirez Boettner, as well as 
congressmen from various parties, make up President Wasmosy's 
entourage. Wasmosy will stay at the Cartagena Hilton. The 
official delegation will participate in various forums through 
15 June. Their return has been scheduled for noon on 16 June. 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

