<F P=100> Peru </F>
<H3> <TI>   Court Names National Election Board President </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Court Names National Election Board President </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY1006222194 Lima Radio Programas del Peru Network in 
Spanish 1800 GMT 10 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY1006222194 </F>
<F P=104>  Lima Radio Programas del Peru Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The plenum of the Peruvian Supreme Court today named 
Ricardo Nunez as its representative to the National Election 
Board. According to the law, Nunez will be the president of the 
National Election Board. 
  Ricardo Nunez, former president of the Supreme Court and 
former rector of the San Martin de Porres University, was the 
senior justice and member of the executive council of the 
judicial branch until 20 April 1992 when he resigned following 
the rupture of the constitutional order. He is currently a labor 
law professor and emeritus rector of the San Martin de Porres 
University, emeritus professor of the San Marcos National 
University, and honorary professor of the National Universities 
of Trujillo, San Antonio, and San Luis Gonzaga. 
  The Supreme Court members also named Alvaro Chocano Marina, 
former president of the Supreme Court, as the alternate 
representative. The official announcement of these appointments 
will be made during a news conference by Supreme Court President 
Luis Serpa Segura in the next few minutes. 

</TEXT>

