<DOCNO> FBIS4-33996 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drlat114_s_94001" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-LAT-94-114 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  11 Jun 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> Uruguay </F>
<H3> <TI>   Argentine, Paraguayan Presidents Depart </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Argentine, Paraguayan Presidents Depart </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY1306171894 Madrid EFE in Spanish 0100 GMT 11 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> PY1306171894 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid EFE </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Montevideo, 10 Jun (EFE) -- Argentine President 
Carlos Menem and Paraguayan President Juan Carlos Wasmosy 
returned tonight to their respective countries after 
participating here in Montevideo in a ceremony to open bids for 
the dredging of the Martin Garcia Channel on the River Plate. 
  The chiefs of state remained for a few hours in the 
Uruguayan 
capital, where they met with Uruguayan President Luis Alberto 
Lacalle and participated in the ceremony during which Uruguayan 
Foreign Minister Sergio Abreu and Argentine Foreign Minister 
Guido Di Tella signed and exchanged the respective documents. 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

