<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ibero-American Heads of State Summit Opens </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ibero-American Heads of State Summit Opens </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Mexican President Addresses Summit </H4>

<F P=102> PA1506010394 Madrid EFE in Spanish 2310 GMT 14 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA1506010394 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid EFE </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cartagena de Indias (Colombia), 14 Jun (EFE) -- The 
main priority of Ibero-American countries is "the well-being of 
those who have less," Mexican President Carlos Salinas de 
Gortari said today at the first working session of the Fourth 
Ibero-American Summit. 
  "It is not possible to advance with inefficient, isolated 
economies, nor is it possible with internationalized economies 
that are socially irresponsible," Salinas de Gortari added. 
According to Salinas de Gortari, "we must insist that economic 
recovery go hand in hand with social reforms." 
  Salinas de Gortari said that he views with optimism 
bilateral 
and multilateral trade agreements signed during the past few 
years by countries of the American Continent because "free trade 
and the just exchange of goods and capital will benefit all of 
us." In addition, he called for a more active presence of 
Ibero-American countries in international organizations, and 
particularly mentioned the World Trade Organization, 
(?affiliated to GATT), which he hopes to chair. 
  Salinas de Gortari expressed his solidarity with Colombia 
over the natural disaster that affected the regions of Cauca and 
Huila last week, which caused more than 1,000 deaths. He also 
congratulated his Colombian counterpart and host, Cesar Gaviria, 
for his election this year as the new OAS secretary general. 
  Salinas de Gortari delivered his speech at the inauguration 
of the Fourth Ibero-American Summit, which was delayed six hours 
because most of the heads of state and government attending the 
event used double and even triple the amount of time they were 
expected to use (seven minutes each). 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-34005 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drlat115aa_94010" </HT>


<HEADER>
