<F P=106> [Report by Orestes Eujelles at Cuban Workers Federation </F>
Headquarters from the "Exclusive" program] 
  [Text] The National Federation of French State Workers, 
made up of civilian employees of the French Armed Forces, will 
issue a medal of solidarity with Cuba. The medal will carry the 
image of Commander Ernesto Che Guevara and bear his historical 
phrase: Until victory always! 
  (Henri Ferry), secretary general of that French 
organization, 
made the announcement during a meeting in the capital with 
high-ranking leaders of the Revolutionary Armed Forces [FAR] 
civilian workers labor union today. (Ferry) emphasized that the 
National Federation of French State Workers will develop a 
strong movement of material and political support to counter the 
U.S. blockade against Cuba. He added: We will support the Cuban 
people until they fully achieve their prosperity. Jose Antonio 
Roque, secretary general of the FAR Civilian Workers' National 
Union, told the visitors about the organization's priority 
tasks, including preparations for their sixth congress scheduled 
for June 1995. 

