<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Vatican denies having signed an agreement with 
the government of Judge Emile Jonassaint to supply wheat to 
Haiti, contrary to what Port-au-Prince has announced. It is an 
unfounded assertion, stated Vatican spokesman (Joaquin Navarro). 
  It should be recalled that on 13 June, the Information 
Ministry announced the Vatican signed an agreement on 27 May to 
supply 75,000 tons of wheat, worth $32 million, with the 
provisional government of Judge Emile Jonassaint. According to 
the Ministry, this agreement was signed in Italy by the foreign 
minister and by Charles David for the Jonassaint government. 
  The Vatican's spokesman, (Joaquin Navarro), asserted, 
however, that no political representative from Haiti was 
received in the Vatican. 

