<F P=100> Barbados </F>
<F P=101> Haiti </F>
<H3> <TI>   Resolution To Inspire Citizens `To Sacrifice Themselves' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Resolution To Inspire Citizens `To Sacrifice Themselves' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL1406222694 Port-au-Prince Radio Metropole in French 1045 
GMT 14 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1406222694 </F>
<F P=104>  Port-au-Prince Radio Metropole </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] On 13 June, the branch of the Senate of the Republic 
led by Senator Bernard Sansaricq restored officers and soldiers 
of the Haitian Army who had been dismissed by the foreign 
occupation forces during the years 1915 and 1916. In a 
resolution adopted on 13 June, the assembly of the contested 18 
January senators declared that the military dismissed in the 
years 1915 to 1916 would enjoy the same rights, prerogatives, 
and privileges granted to the retired members of the Haitian 
Armed Forces. This decision, which had mere symbolic value, is 
aimed at encouraging Haitians to sacrifice themselves for the 
glory and greatness of the homeland. Here is an excerpt of the 
resolution presented by Sen. Cadet: 
  [Begin Cadet recording] Considering that it is necessary to 
encourage and stimulate Haitians to sacrifice themselves for the 
honor and glory of the homeland; considering that it is 
necessary to restore the memory of the members of the Haitian 
Army dismissed during the years 1915 and 1916 by the foreign 
occupation forces, and to correct such a grave injustice, the 
Senate of the Republic has decided on the following: 
  Article 1. The dissolution of the Haitian Army, Navy, and 
police force by foreign occupation forces during the years 1915 
and 1916 is null and void. 
  Article 2. The members of the Army, Navy, and the Haitian 
police force, dismissed during the years 1915 and 1916, are 
restored with their respective ranks to the Haitian Armed 
Forces. [end recording] 
  That was an excerpt from the resolution voted on 13 June by 
the branch of the Senate led by Sen. Bernard Sansaricq. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

