<H3> <TI>   Funds for Repaying Foreign Debt Moved To Finance Elections </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Funds for Repaying Foreign Debt Moved To Finance Elections </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY1406033094 Rio de Janeiro O GLOBO in Portuguese 10 Jun 94 
p 4 </F>

<F P=103> PY1406033094 </F>
<F P=104>  Rio de Janeiro O GLOBO </F>
<F P=105>  Portuguese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Brasilia -- The government will use approximately 
$160 million from the funds allocated for payment of the foreign 
debt to supply the Superior Electoral Court [TSE] with the funds 
needed to pay election expenses. The agreement was made 
yesterday by Planning Minister Beni Veras, PFL [Liberal Front 
Party] senator for Paraiba Raymundo Lyra -- the president of the 
Budget Committee of Congress -- and TSE President Sepulveda 
Pertence. The government chose this solution because the $160 
million that was to have been used for repaying the debt can be 
resupplied in August, once the budget bill has been voted on. 
  "If it needs the funds, the government can submit a message 
to Congress asking for inclusion of a supplemental credit in the 
budget. The budget will have been voted on by August, and there 
will be no problem," Lyra said. 

</TEXT>

