<F P=102>   PY1406164694 Sao Paulo AGENCIA ESTADO in Portuguese 0018 GMT 
12 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY1406164694 </F>
<F P=104>  Sao Paulo AGENCIA ESTADO </F>
<F P=105>  Portuguese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Brasilia, 12 Jun (AE) -- At 1900 today the Superior 
Electoral Court (TSE) closed registration for presidential 
candidates. Only one party registered candidates over the 
weekend: the Brazilian Party for the Defense of Women's Rights 
(PBDDM) [Partido Brasileiro de Defesa dos Direitos da Mulher]. 
The party's presidential candidate is Aldenora de Sa Porto and 
the vice presidential candidate is Nina Maria Alexim. The PBDDM 
has been provisionally registered, and the registration of its 
candidates is subject to approval by the TSE. Aldenora de Sa 
Porto is the 11th registered candidate. 
  The others are: Luiz Inacio Lula da Silva (PT) [Workers 
Party], Fernando Henrique Cardoso (PSDB) [Brazilian Social 
Democracy Party], Orestes Quercia (PMDB) [Brazilian Democratic 
Movement Party], Leonel Brizola (PDT) [Democratic Labor Party], 
Esperidiao Amin (PPR) [Progressive Renewal Party], Flavio Rocha 
(PL) [Liberal Party], Eneas Carneiro (Prona) [Party for the 
Redefinition of the National Order], Hernani Goulart Fortuna 
(PSC) [Social Christian Party], Walter Queiroz (PRN) [National 
Reconstruction Party], and Caetano Matano (PT do B) [Brazilian 
Workers Party]. 

</TEXT>

