<H3> <TI>   President Orders Implementation of `Equal Salary Plan' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    President Orders Implementation of `Equal Salary Plan' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY1306211294 Sao Paulo AGENCIA ESTADO in Portuguese 0022 GMT 
11 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY1306211294 </F>
<F P=104>  Sao Paulo AGENCIA ESTADO </F>
<F P=105>  Portuguese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] Brasilia, 10 Jun (AE) -- Just one day after 
receiving a report from the military ministers, in which they 
warn of instability among the troops over low salaries, 
President Itamar Franco ordered Federal Administration Secretary 
Romildo Canhim to begin working next week with the Finance 
Ministry on a timetable to implement the equal salary plan among 
the three government branches. 
  This decision, which directly benefits the military and 
civil 
servants of the executive branch, was made during a nearly 
two-hour meeting with the four military ministers. 
  "It is impossible to maintain the current salary scale," 
President Itamar admitted during the meeting that was requested 
by the ministers who expressed total support for the equal 
salary treatment law. [passage omitted] 
  Federal Administration Secretary Canhim said he has no idea 
how long it will take to fully implement the equal salary plan. 
"Everything depends on the revenue collection capability, which 
we will now discuss with the Finance Ministry," he said. 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

