<F P=106> [From the "Caracol's 0600 to 0900" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Attention: The first problem of the Fourth 
Ibero-American Summit in Cartagena arose when terrorists blew up 
the Caracol and Radio Cadena Nacional [RCN] repeater stations. 
The attack, for which no group has claimed responsibility, 
destroyed the stations' tuning boxes and insulators. Caracol is 
using special emergency frequencies and mobile telephones to 
cover the presidential summit. 

