<F P=100> Chile </F>
<H3> <TI>   Defense Chief Comments on Professional Army </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Defense Chief Comments on Professional Army </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY1406203494 Santiago Television Nacional de Chile Imagen 
Internacional in Spanish 1800 GMT 14 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY1406203494 </F>
<F P=104>  Santiago Television Nacional de Chile Imagen 
Internacional </F>

<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] National Defense Chief of Staff Jorge Patricio 
Arancibia has stated that the Armed Forces favor compulsory 
military service because it helps to safeguard society. 
  Vice Admiral Arancibia said military service enables youths 
to acquire values and principles, and helps them to understand 
professional training. 
  Arancibia said of the 121,000 who registered in 1993, only 
29,400 were drafted. He added that the Army and the Air Force 
have already reduced military service to one year, while the 
Navy is studying this possibility. 
  Asked about the Argentine decision to create a professional 
Army, he said the Chilean Armed Forces should also study this 
issue. He declined to say if the Argentine decision constitutes 
a threat because Argentina has yet to implement this decision. 
Arancibia admitted, however, that a professional Army is more 
effective than a nonprofessional Army although it is more costly. 

</TEXT>

