<F P=100> Chile </F>
<H3> <TI>   Investigative Police Arrest Buschmann </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Investigative Police Arrest Buschmann </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY1506001794 Madrid EFE in Spanish 1803 GMT 14 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> PY1506001794 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid EFE </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Santiago, 14 Jun (EFE) -- The Chilean Investigative 
Police arrested Sergio Buschmann today at the international 
airport. Buschmann, who has been a fugitive since 1987, returned 
voluntarily from Nicaragua. 
  More than 200 peple were waiting at the airport for 
Buschmann, who arrived from Costa Rica after a three-hour delay. 
Among those waiting for him were leftist opposition leaders who 
went to the airport to express their solidarity with him. 
  Buschmann, a 51-year-old theater actor and one of the 
founders of the Manuel Rodriguez Patriotic Front (FPMR), was 
arrested during the past military regime. He was accused of 
leading an operation to conceal weapons the FPMR had smuggled 
into Chile in 1986. 
  The following year he escaped from prison and left the 
country clandestinely. Today he is returning to exercise, as he 
said, his legitimate right to defend himself and to resume his 
life legally. 

</TEXT>

