<F P=106> [Interview with President Fidel Castro by unidentified </F>
reporter in Cartagena de Indias, Colombia, on 13 June -- 
recorded] 
  [Text] [Castro] We have made progress in Cuba. Everyone 
there is waiting to hear the presidents' positions. 
  [Reporter] Will you meet with Honduran President Carlos 
Roberto Reina? He wants to meet with you. 
  [Castro] I will gladly meet with anyone who wants to meet 
with me. 
  [Reporter] Do you think you will achieve Cuba's reentry into 
the OAS? 
  [Castro] Well, I don't know. 
  [Reporter] Will you present that position? 
  [Castro] No, I will not. 
  [Reporter] What is Cuba's interest [words indistinct] 
Honduras? [words indistinct] 
  [Castro] We have some things we want to say, but they will 
have to wait until tomorrow. 

</TEXT>

