<H3> <TI>   Castro Arrives in Colombia, Meets Press </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Castro Arrives in Colombia, Meets Press </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL1406121994 Havana Radio Progreso Network in Spanish 1100 
GMT 14 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1406121994 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Progreso Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "First Thing" program] </F>
  [Text] Last night, Commander in Chief Fidel Castro arrived 
in Cartagena de Indias, Colombia, to attend the fourth 
Ibero-American summit 14-15 June. Fidel arrived in the company 
of Ricardo Alarcon de Quesada, president of the National 
Assembly of the People's Government, and Foreign Minister 
Roberto Robaina. Fidel was greeted at the foot of the Cubana 
plane by Colombian Foreign Minister Noemi Sanin and writer 
Gabriel Garcia Marquez, winner of the Nobel Prize for 
Literature. Colombian Justice Minister Andres Gonzalez and 
Communications Minister William Jaramillo were also present. 
  After reviewing the honor guard and speaking with 
approximately 20 reporters, Fidel said he was very pleased to be 
in Colombia and replied to a question by saying it would be too 
optimistic to hope the U.S. blockade would end during the 
summit. Fidel added that he has several things he wants to say 
but we have to wait until 14 June, when he will address the 
heads of state of the 21 Ibero-American nations. 
  Last night, along the route of the caravan taking Fidel and 
Foreign Minister Sanin to the hotel, numerous people gathered to 
shout support and welcome slogans. Some of the slogans 
displayed along the route of the caravan read: Welcome Fidel! 
With Cuba for all Times! 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

