<F P=100> Venezuela </F>
<H3> <TI>   Seven Banks Closed After Central Bank Decision </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Seven Banks Closed After Central Bank Decision </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA1406170594 Paris AFP in Spanish 1520 GMT 14 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA1406170594 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Caracas, 14 Jun (AFP) -- According to similar 
reports issued in Caracas today, seven Venezuelan commercial 
banks closed their doors today "until further notice" following 
a decision by the Central Bank of Venezuela to exclude them from 
clearinghouse activities. 
  Although the source did not deny nor confirm the news to 
AFP, 
its reporters were able to confirm that the Construccion, 
Barinas, Maracaibo, La Guaira, Metropolitano, Bancor, 
Hipotecario de Occidente banks and the Sociedad Financiera 
Fiveca remained closed today. Despite the fact that the banks 
were closed, their employees were working while hundreds of 
customers protested at the doors. 
  These seven banks and Latino Bank -- the country's second 
largest bank, in which the government intervened in January and 
which reopened in April with losses of $5 billion -- have 
received financial assistance amounting to $4.300 billion since 
February to prevent their collapse. 

</TEXT>

