<F P=101> Brazil </F>
<H3> <TI>   Support for Lula Decreasing; Others Stable </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Support for Lula Decreasing; Others Stable </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY1406020194 Rio de Janeiro JORNAL DO BRASIL in Portuguese 
12 Jun 94 p 1 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> PY1406020194 </F>
<F P=104>  Rio de Janeiro JORNAL DO BRASIL </F>
<F P=105>  Portuguese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A poll conducted by Vox Populi between 4 and 7 June 
is published exclusively by JORNAL DO BRASIL. It indicates that 
compared to the poll conducted in May, support for Workers Party 
candidate Luiz Inacio Lula da Silva has dropped by 5 points. 
His support dropped from 41 percent to 36 percent, but the 
votes lost by Lula have not been absorbed by any of his main 
rivals. Support for Fernando Henrique Cardoso, of the Brazilian 
Social Democracy Party, remains at 17 percent and he continues 
in second place. Democratic Labor Party candidate Leonel 
Brizola still holds third place and is supported by 7 percent of 
the voters. Those who will annul their votes or who still do 
not know for whom they will vote total 29 percent. The poll 
also indicates that President Itamar Franco's support for 
Cardoso is important and that strikes staged by the Sole Workers 
Center harm Lula's image. 

</TEXT>

