<F P=101> Cuba </F>
<H3> <TI>   PRENSA LATINA Reports Castro Speech at Summit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    PRENSA LATINA Reports Castro Speech at Summit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA1406190194 Havana PRENSA LATINA in Spanish 1709 GMT 14 Jun 
94 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> PA1406190194 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana PRENSA LATINA </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cartagena de Indias, 14 Jun (PL) -- Cuban President 
Fidel Castro said here today that the time has come to demand 
that the United States abide by the UN resolutions condemning 
the U.S. blockade imposed on that Caribbean island. 
  He also demanded a withdrawal from the Navy Base at 
Guantanamo, Cuba, from the Panama Canal, and other Latin 
American countries in his speech before the Fourth 
Ibero-American Summit meeting here. 
  The Cuban leader referred to the so-called hemispheric event 
scheduled by the U.S. Government in Miami in December, and he 
said it would provide an opportunity to demand an end to the 
"criminal and unfair blockade against Cuba." 
  After referring to the summit agenda, he said that if those 
topics are discussed, "Cuba wishes them success," but he noted 
that everything could boil down to "an attempt to establish a 
course in the hemisphere to isolate Cuba; to take control of 
markets in Latin America and the Caribbean; and to check Europe, 
Japan, and the rest of the world." 
  In that case, he added, one would have to paraphrase Jose 
Marti, a Cuban national hero, when a similar event was held in 
Washington 105 years ago: "The time has come for Spanish 
America to declare its second independence." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

