<H3> <TI>   Robaina Not Disappointed By Lack of Blockade Remarks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Robaina Not Disappointed By Lack of Blockade Remarks </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA1506190494 Havana PRENSA LATINA in Spanish 1715 GMT 15 Jun 
94 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> PA1506190494 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana PRENSA LATINA </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cartagena de Indias, 15 Jun (PL) -- Cuban Foreign 
Minister Roberto Robaina denied today his country feels 
disappointed by the development of the Fourth Ibero-American 
Summit taking place in this Colombian Caribbean city. 
  When questioned by the press on the lack of a statement at 
the important meeting on the U.S. blockade against his country, 
Robaina replied: "We have no reason to feel disappointed, and 
our conversations regarding this have continued progressing." 
  The chief of Cuban diplomacy was approached by PRENSA LATINA 
reporters and two other media representatives at the conclusion 
of the official photo session of the 21 Ibero-American nations' 
foreign ministers, before the initiation of the second and last 
session of the summit. 

</TEXT>

