<H3> <TI>   Robaina Terms Salinas' Visit `Very Successful' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Robaina Terms Salinas' Visit `Very Successful' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA1506141594 Havana PRENSA LATINA in Spanish 1344 GMT 14 Jun 
94 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> PA1506141594 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana PRENSA LATINA </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cartagena de Indias, 14 Jun (PL) -- Cuban Foreign 
Minister Roberto Robaina described Mexican President Carlos 
Salinas de Gortari's visit to Cuba, one day before the 
initiation of the Fourth Ibero-American Presidential Summit, as 
very successful. 
  Upon his arrival in this city, which has close similarities 
to Havana, Robaina told PRENSA LATINA that Salinas' visit had 
shown the Cubans' and Mexicans'-- especially their governments' 
-- capacity and will to increase bilateral ties. 
  He considered it especially significant that the Aztec 
country had respected the path taken by the island to initiate 
its economic changes and had not allowed Cuba to be left alone 
in these moments. 
  His stay in Havana, Robaina added, was very intense and 
provided the Cuban delegation to the fourth summit a head start 
in the collateral bilateral relations program and the 
celebration itself. 
  The Cuban foreign minister believes the activity of the 
Mexican leader in Havana furthered practical steps to be taken 
in a new situation for both countries. During his stay, 
important agreements were signed and still others are in a 
process of negotiations. 
  In this sense, he considered the signing of the agreements 
as 
very important, especially the agreement on the telephone 
system. Agreements in other sectors, such as in the cement, 
textile, tile, and sanitary furniture manufacturing industries, 
had also been advanced. Finally, he recalled that both leaders 
had valued their encounter as being courageous, deep, fruitful, 
and extremely friendly. 
  Robaina is a member of the official Cuban delegation to the 
Fourth Ibero-American Summit, headed by President Fidel Castro. 
The Cuban president was received here by an enthusiastic 
solidarity group which awaited, since very early today, his 
arrival close to the Hilton Hotel, where the presidents have 
been staying. 

</TEXT>

