<F P=100> Nicaragua </F>
<H3> <TI>   Officials, World Bank To Discuss Loan Request </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Officials, World Bank To Discuss Loan Request </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA1506233994 </F>
<F P=103> PA1506233994 </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
BFN 

    [Editorial Report] Managua Radio Nicaragua Network in 
Spanish at 1200 GMT on 13 June reports a government delegation 
will arrive in Paris this week to meet with members of the 
advisory board of the World Bank to analyze the impact of 
international cooperation on Nicaragua's process of economic 
stabilization. Jose Evenor Taboada Arana, president of the 
Nicaraguan Central Bank, has said the meeting will be held in 
Paris on 16 and 17 June to confirm a $50 million loan promised 
to Nicaragua over the next three years. Nicaragua will also seek 
a $200 million loan to accelerate the peace process in 
Nicaragua, Taboada added. 

</TEXT>

