<F P=100> Panama </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Suspends Flights to, From Haiti </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Suspends Flights to, From Haiti </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA1606004294 Panama City TVN Television Network in Spanish 
0000 GMT 16 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1606004294 </F>
<F P=104>  Panama City TVN Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Seven O'Clock National Newscast"] </F>
  [Excerpt] Acting President Guillermo Ford Boyd chaired the 
scheduled cabinet meeting at the Presidential Palace. Deputy 
Foreign Minister Carlos Cordero announced that the government 
will take steps against Haiti. 
  [Begin recording] [Cordero] In accordance with 
recommendations made at the recent meeting of foreign ministers 
in Belen de Para, Brazil, within the context of the OAS General 
Assembly meeting, Panama issued a decree prohibiting all 
commercial flights between Panama and Haiti. Acting President 
Ford signed the decree that also prohibits the issuance of 
takeoff permits for any flights heading for Haiti. 
  [Unidentified reporter] What criteria were taken into 
account? 
  [Cordero] The OAS recommendations. This is another 
diplomatic effort directed at solving the Haitian problem. [end 
recording] [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

