<F P=100> Panama </F>
<H3> <TI>   Endara Requests Readmission to Rio Group </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Endara Requests Readmission to Rio Group </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA1506144094 Panama City Circuito RPC Television in Spanish 
2300 GMT 14 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1506144094 </F>
<F P=104>  Panama City Circuito RPC Television </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "RPC Television News" newscast] </F>
  [Excerpt] [passage omitted] President Guillermo Endara has 
said that our country must be readmitted to the Rio Group, from 
which it was expelled when the military dictatorship ruled 
Panama. 
  [Begin Endara recording] I wish to bring to the attention of 
the appropriate heads of state a topic that I believe is of 
great importance and fairness for Panama and the Panamanian 
people. I am referring to the readmission of Panama as a full 
member of the permanent group for political dialogue and unity, 
better known as the Rio Group. 
  In February 1988, when Dictator Noriega overthrew the 
makeshift civilian president, right here in Cartagena, the Group 
of Eight suspended Panama from the group disclosing before the 
whole world the real anti-democratic form of government ruling 
my country at that time. I am taking this opportunity, this 
very important meeting, to express my wishes because it is my 
most heartfelt desire to see my people completely incorporated 
within Latin America before I leave office. 
  Today, having consolidated democracy, we have the moral 
authority to request that we be rightfully readmitted to a group 
that is very important. This will contribute to strengthening 
our integrating capacity for South and Central America, this 
latter region that, after many sacrifices, deserves the greatest 
praise. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

