<F P=100> CARIBBEAN </F>
<F P=101> Cuba </F>
<H3> <TI>   Summit Participants `Perplexed' by Castro's 2d Speech </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Summit Participants `Perplexed' by Castro's 2d Speech </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL1506145794 Havana Radio Reloj Network in Spanish 1400 GMT 
15 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1506145794 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Reloj Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] The Cuba issue is apparently the main course 
today during the second and last day of deliberations at the 
Fourth Ibero-American Summit, which is currently under way at 
the seaside resort of Cartagena de Indias, Colombia. Before the 
conference, the media and one or two leaders repeatedly referred 
to the island -- mostly in an insidious way -- it was reported 
by a PRENSA LATINA news agency report. 
  During the summit's inauguration, once the speeches before 
the plenary session had concluded, Cuban President Fidel Castro 
demanded -- in a second speech -- respect for his country and 
recognition for the people given their tenacious resistance to 
the U.S. blockade. 
  The Cuban leader's surprisingly strong reaction perplexed 
most of the participants at the Cartagena de Indias meeting 
because they were suddenly confronted with a reality that cannot 
possibly be ignored, even if they tried to. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

