<H3> <TI>   Raul Castro Letter Marks Western Army Anniversary </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Raul Castro Letter Marks Western Army Anniversary </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL1506130194 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 0900 
GMT 15 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1506130194 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Army General Raul Castro Ruz, minister of the 
Revolutionary Armed Forces [FAR], has chaired [as heard] the 
ceremony marking the 35th [as heard] anniversary of the creation 
of the Western Army. The ceremony was held at the Playa Giron 
Fighter Brigade in San Antonio de los Banos, Havana. During the 
ceremony, Division General Nestor Lopez Cuba, chief of the FAR 
political directorate, read a letter of congratulations from 
Raul in which he acknowledged that they have satisfactorily 
fulfilled complex and important missions for three decades. The 
letter praises the fact that the Western Army has had 
significant participation in important tasks such as 
internationalist missions in Angola and Ethiopia, supporting the 
food program, and preparing the theater of operations, among 
others. 

</TEXT>

