<H3> <TI>   Thermoelectric Plant Tests Begin Following Repairs </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Thermoelectric Plant Tests Begin Following Repairs </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL1506171494 Havana Radio Reloj Network in Spanish 1400 GMT 
15 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1506171494 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Reloj Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Carlos Manuel de Cespedes Thermoelectric Plant 
in Cienfuegos has begun tests to start its machinery after 
almost 60 days of extensive repairs to Unit No. 2. Specialists 
from the Carlos Manuel de Cespedes Thermoelectric Plant reported 
that the work was satisfactorily carried out, which consisted of 
mainly a complete overhaul to the boiler, auxiliary equipment, 
and the pump. The most complex work carried out at the plant 
involved cleaning the sea water intake canal for treatment of 
the Czech units. 
  Once maintenance work has ended at the Carlos Manuel de 
Cespedes Thermoelectric Plant in Cienfuegos Province, all 
efforts will be entirely dedicated to repairs at Unit No.1 -- 
currently underway -- for its subsequent synchronization with 
the system by year end. 

</TEXT>

