<H3> <TI>   Water Plant Breakdowns To Affect Municipalities </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Water Plant Breakdowns To Affect Municipalities </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL1506222494 Havana Radio Reloj Network in Spanish 1941 GMT 
15 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1506222494 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Reloj Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] On Thursday, between the hours of 0500 and 1800 
local time, the water supply of several municipalities in the 
capital will be affected by breakdowns at the water treatment 
plant. The Havana City Waterworks Directorate advised that the 
areas affected will be: Regla, with the exception of the El 
Modelo neighborhood; Alamar; Camilo Cienfuegos; the Panamerican 
villas in La Habana del Este; the rum and yeast factories; the 
El Lucero cream plant; the Rene Ramos technological center in 
Aroyo Naranjo; the Villa Maria neighborhood, Guanabacoa; the 
Vista Alegre neighborhood, Diez de Octubre; and the San Miguel 
del Padron area. The waterworks directorate encourages 
residents to store water until service is restored. 

</TEXT>

