<H3> <TI>   Police Chief Affirms Support for Cedras </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Police Chief Affirms Support for Cedras </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA1506164494 Paris AFP in Spanish 1406 GMT 15 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA1506164494 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Port-au-Prince, 15 Jun (AFP) -- Lieutenant Colonel 
Joseph Michel Francois, chief of police in the Haitian capital, 
confirmed last night his loyalty and support for Army Commander 
General Raoul Cedras. 
  The chief of police also issued a communique condemning the 
position of his brother Evans, who, yesterday in Santo Domingo, 
demanded the resignation of Gen. Cedras to avoid a U.S. invasion 
of Haiti. 
  Evans Francois, a former diplomat who claims to be one of 
the 
masterminds of the 30 September 1991 coup d'etat against 
President Jean-Bertrand Aristide, also said he fears for the 
life of his brother. 

</TEXT>

