<F P=100> Haiti </F>
<H3> <TI>   Lt. Col. Francois Not Bound by Brother's Stand </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Lt. Col. Francois Not Bound by Brother's Stand </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL1506174394 Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio in French 1030 
GMT 15 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1506174394 </F>
<F P=104>  Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Lieutenant Colonel Joseph Michel Francois has 
reacted to the statement made by his brother Evans Francois on a 
sister radio station. Lt. Col. Joseph Michel Francois informs 
the public in general and the members of the Haitian Armed 
Forces [FADH] in particular that his brother's stand does not 
bind him in any way. Fear or any other emotions engendered by 
some foreign threat do not exist and will not exist in him, Lt. 
Col. Joseph Michel Francois points out. This is why he reproves 
the unpleasant and untimely statements made about his chief, 
statements that reflect on the institution to which Lt. Col. 
Francois belongs and on his country, which need the solidarity 
and unity of all its sons in these stormy times. [passage 
omitted] 

</TEXT>

