<H3> <TI>   Spokesman Describes `Polarization' Within FRAPH </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Spokesman Describes `Polarization' Within FRAPH </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL1506212594 Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio in French 1030 
GMT 15 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1506212594 </F>
<F P=104>  Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] What is going on within the Revolutionary Front for 
the Promotion and Progress of Haiti [FRAPH]? In a press release, 
the front has forbidden Mr. Louis Jodel Chambelain from making 
any statements on behalf of FRAPH. The general director of the 
front, namely Paul Arthur Fleurival Lahens, was contacted by 
phone and he spoke of polarization within the administrative 
staff. 
  [Begin Lahens recording, in Creole] In any political 
movement 
in gestation, there is something called polarization. As you 
know, the front includes Emmanuel Constant, secretary general of 
the organization; Louis Jodel Chamblain, national coordinator; 
and Paul Arthur Fleurival Lahens, general director of the front. 
  There is no problem. As I told you, there is only a 
polarization problem. But once it is a question of cooperation, 
everybody can get together. Certainly there are some mistakes. 
As the saying goes: To err is human. People may make mistakes, 
but they must not be grave mistakes. There is always a way to 
reconcile. We are only waiting for the appropriate time so there 
can be rallying cry. Then you will see that there is really 
nothing wrong. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

