<F P=100> Brazil </F>
<H3> <TI>   Lula Vows To Negotiate Debt `Directly With Presidents' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Lula Vows To Negotiate Debt `Directly With Presidents' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY1606013894 Sao Paulo O ESTADO DE SAO PAULO in Portuguese 
15 Jun 94 p A6 </F>

<F P=103> PY1606013894 </F>
<F P=104>  Sao Paulo O ESTADO DE SAO PAULO </F>
<F P=105>  Portuguese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] During an evening debate with the Jewish community 
on 13 June, PT [Workers Party] presidential candidate Luiz 
Inacio Lula da Silva said he, like the Jews, is a "survivor." 
He said: "I survived the starvation war in the northeastern 
region." He included something new in his government proposal, 
saying: "I will negotiate the foreign debt directly with the 
presidents." He added: "I will contact U.S. President Bill 
Clinton because I know he is more sensitive to the social 
situation resulting from our debt." He criticized the current 
Brazilian foreign policy, saying: "We are important enough to 
play the international power game, yet all we do is run after 
the ball." 
  Lula and Jose Dirceu, the PT candidate for the governorship 
of Sao Paulo State, kicked off a series of candidate debates 
sponsored by the Sao Paulo Israeli Federation at the Hebrew 
Club. Progressive Renewal Party presidential candidate 
Esperidiao Amin and Luiz Antonio de Medeiros, the Popular Party 
candidate for state governor, will participate on 27 June. 
Brazilian Social Democracy Party candidates Fernando Henrique 
Cardoso and Mario Covas are scheduled for 8 August, and Orestes 
Quercia and Barros Munhoz for 22 August. 

</TEXT>

