<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Chamber of Deputies Strips Deputy of Rights </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY1606013994 Sao Paulo AGENCIA ESTADO in Portuguese 2030 GMT 
15 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY1606013994 </F>
<F P=104>  Sao Paulo AGENCIA ESTADO </F>
<F P=105>  Portuguese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Brasilia, 15 Jun (AE) -- With 312 votes in favor, 59 
against, 15 abstentions, and one void, the Chamber of Deputies 
has stripped Deputy Jose Geraldo Ribeiro (PMDB-MG) [Brazilian 
Democratic Movement Party-Minas Gerais State] of his political 
rights. The Congressional Investigating Committee, looking into 
the irregular handling of budget funds, found Ribeiro guilty of 
misusing federal budget funds and of unlawful accumulation of 
wealth. The Chamber of Deputies is now voting on the suspension 
of Deputy Flavio Derzi (PP-MS) [Popular Party-Mato Grosso do Sul 
State]. Derzi also is charged with irregular handling of budget 
funds. 

</TEXT>

