<H3> <TI>   Foreign Minister Doubts U.S. Will Suspend Aid </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Minister Doubts U.S. Will Suspend Aid </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA1606132694 Managua Sistema Nacional de Television Network 
in Spanish 0200 GMT 14 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1606132694 </F>
<F P=104>  Managua Sistema Nacional de Television Network 
in Spanish 0200 GMT 14 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=105> Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "National Newcast"] </F>
  [Text] Nicaragua does not believe the United States will 
suspend its aid again. Should this happen, however, it would be 
a grave mistake, affecting a country trying to consolidate its 
democracy, Foreign Minister Ernesto Leal said upon arriving in 
Cartagena de Indias to participate in the Fourth Ibero-American 
Summit. 
  Although the aid has been objected to by Republican 
congressmen due to unresolved claims for property 
indemnification filed by U.S. citizens, Minister Leal said the 
Helms-Gonzalez Amendment has been misinterpreted. He added that 
when a country has an adequate indemnification system, as in the 
case of Nicaragua, there should be no major problems. 

</TEXT>

