<F P=100> Chile </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Ministry Confirms 9 Cubans at Consulate </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Ministry Confirms 9 Cubans at Consulate </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY1506191794 Madrid EFE in Spanish 1731 GMT 15 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> PY1506191794 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid EFE </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Santiago, 15 Jun (EFE) -- Sources at the Chilean 
presidential palace of La Moneda have reported that the group of 
Cubans who today entered the Chilean Consulate General in Havana 
consists of seven young men, one woman, and a child. 
  According to the same sources, who did not provide any 
further details, a full report on this event will be released 
within the next few hours. 
  The Chilean Foreign Ministry had already confirmed the entry 
of the group of Cubans into the Chilean Consulate, and added 
that President Eduardo Frei and Foreign Minister Carlos Figueroa 
have already been informed about the event. 
  Frei and his foreign minister are participating in the 
Fourth 
Ibero-American Summit in Cartagena de Indias, Colombia. 
  This is the third time Cubans have rushed into an embassy in 
Havana over the past 20 days. They had done so before at the 
Belgian and German embassies. 

</TEXT>

