<F P=100> Brazil </F>
<H3> <TI>   PT President Rejects Alliance With Sarney </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    PT President Rejects Alliance With Sarney </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY1606005194 Rio de Janeiro O GLOBO in Portuguese 11 Jun 94 
p 3 </F>

<F P=103> PY1606005194 </F>
<F P=104>  Rio de Janeiro O GLOBO </F>
<F P=105>  Portuguese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Article by Walter Falceta Jr.] </F>
  [Text] Sao Paulo -- The PT [Workers Party] will not make 
any political agreement with Senator Jose Sarney (PMDB-AP) 
[Brazilian Democratic Movement Party - Amapa]. This was reported 
early yesterday evening by PT President Rui Falcao (state deputy 
for SP) [Sao Paulo]. A day earlier, PT presidential candidate 
Luiz Inacio Lula da Silva said that he would accept Sarney's 
support. Lula said that the PT could not refuse to talk with the 
former president and that he will resume the north-south railway 
construction begun by Sarney. 
  "There will be no agreement with Senator Sarney. The PT has 
not and will not seek him. We cannot forbid, however, anyone 
from demonstrating admiration for our candidate," Falcao said 
after the weekly meeting of the PT national executive board. 
  Falcao, one of the leaders of the most radical PT wing, said 
the party cannot make an agreement with Sarney because his 
government was marked by recession and by the liberal 
distribution of radio and television stations [in exchange for 
political support]. Falcao believes that a political alliance 
between Lula and Sarney is "unthinkable." 
  "The PT demonstrated what it thinks of Sarney when it 
struggled with all its might to prevent him from remaining in 
power for five years. No PT deputy voted for the extension of 
his term in office," the PT president said. 
  The party is not disdaining Lula's idea of wanting Sarney's 
support, Falcao said, adding that Lula and the PT agree on one 
point: The objective is to win the votes of Sarney's followers. 
  Despite the meeting held on 8 June between Deputies Aloizio 
Mercadante (PT-SP) and Jose Sarney Filho (PFL-MA) [Liberal Front 
Party - Maranhao] to discuss an alliance between Lula and 
Sarney, Falcao said there has never been an understanding on the 
subject. He said the "informal talks" between Aloizio and Sarney 
Filho were misinterpreted. According to Falcao, the PT's 
strategy will be to maintain direct contacts with Sarney's 
followers and convince them that Lula's government platform is 
the best to get the country through the crisis. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

