<H3> <TI>   Presidents, Officials React to Castro Speech </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Presidents, Officials React to Castro Speech </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Reschedule Lunch To Discuss Issue </H4>

<F P=102> PA1506201594 Santa Fe de Bogota Emisoras Caracol Network in 
Spanish 1737 GMT 15 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1506201594 </F>
<F P=104>  Santa Fe de Bogota Emisoras Caracol Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] There has been a change in the agenda of the 
presidents and heads of government. A lunch had been scheduled 
at the Fishing Club around noon today. However, in the wake of 
numerous statements on individual positions each president has 
regarding the Cuban issue, the U.S. economic blockade, and 
President Fidel Castro's unexpected speech yesterday, the 
leaders decided to meet or have lunch here at the convention 
center to discuss, behind closed doors, the positions presented 
on the Cuban case. 
  Later on, at approximately 2100 GMT, the last working 
session 
will be held. Tonight, Colombian President Cesar Gaviria 
Trujillo and Argentine President Carlos Saul Menem will close 
the event. They will be the only speakers at the ceremony. 

</TEXT>

