<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Brazil's Franco Leaves After Nephew's Death </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Brazil's Franco Leaves After Nephew's Death </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY1506152594 Sao Paulo AGENCIA ESTADO in Portuguese 1450 GMT 
15 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY1506152594 </F>
<F P=104>  Sao Paulo AGENCIA ESTADO </F>
<F P=105>  Portuguese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Brasilia, 15 Jun (AE) -- Presidential spokesman 
Fernando Costa announced that President Itamar Franco has been 
deeply shaken by the death of his nephew Ariosto Franco in 
Cartagena, Colombia. The president was informed early this 
morning that his nephew had suffered a heart attack. 
  Franco and the members of his entourage have canceled every 
appointment scheduled for today, and are preparing to return to 
Brazil as soon as Ariosto Franco's body is released. Franco's 
trip to Ecuador, which was scheduled to start on 16 June, has 
thus been canceled. A medical bulletin will soon be released on 
the death of the president's nephew. 
  [At 1438 GMT AGENCIA ESTADO adds that "in addition to being 
President Franco's private secretary," the 36-year-old Ariosto 
Carlos Franco "had been living with the president at Alvorada 
Palace."] 

</TEXT>

