<H3> <TI>   Foreign Ministers To Meet in Bogota 6 Aug </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Ministers To Meet in Bogota 6 Aug </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA1606033894 Hamburg DPA in Spanish 1555 GMT 15 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA1606033894 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cartagena de Indias (Colombia), 15 Jun (DPA) -- The 
organizers of the Fourth Ibero-American Summit of chiefs of 
state and government, currently taking place in the Colombian 
city of Cartagena de Indias, have announced that a new 
Ibero-American summit, this time of foreign ministers, will be 
held on 6 August in Santa Fe de Bogota. 
  The objective of this new meeting is to develop a suitable 
mechanism to follow up the Ibero-American agenda, which is 
currently delineating new commercial integration and social 
development strategies to be included in the document that will 
be released at the closing of the presidential meeting. 
  The chiefs of state and government, who are currently 
meeting 
at this Caribbean seaside resort, will officially convene this 
new meeting of foreign ministers. 
  The new summit will entrust the 22 Latin American, 
Caribbean, 
and Iberian foreign ministers with the preparation and 
disclosure of suggestions for the Santa Fe de Bogota foreign 
ministers meeting, which will take place the day before the 
inauguration of the new Colombian president who will be elected 
on 19 June. 

</TEXT>

