<H4>    Dominican Vice President on Haitian Situation </H4>

<F P=102> PA1606172294 Santa Fe de Bogota Emisoras Caracol Network in 
Spanish 1409 GMT 16 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1606172294 </F>
<F P=104>  Santa Fe de Bogota Emisoras Caracol Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report on interview with Dominican Vice President Carlos </F>
Morales Troncoso by unidentified reporter in Cartagena de Indias 
on 16 June -- recorded] 
  [Text] [Reporter] Amid complications, restrictions, and 
endless competition with the local media, we were able to 
approach Dominican Vice President Carlos Morales, and ask him 
about the Cuban [as heard] situation. 
  [Morales] What is not being said is that we, Dominicans, are 
the hardest hit by the Haitian situation. As a result of the 
continuing Haitian problem, our country has over 1 million 
illegal Haitian residents, which constitutes an extremely heavy 
burden. We support a prompt, but democratic solution. 

</TEXT>

