<H3> <TI>   Cuba To Host Ninth Ibero-American Summit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Cuba To Host Ninth Ibero-American Summit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL1606132694 Havana Radio Progreso Network in Spanish 1100 
GMT 16 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1606132694 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Progreso Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "First Thing" program] </F>
  [Text] On 15 June, Cuba was officially appointed the seat 
of the Ninth Ibero-American Heads of State Summit in 1999 
according to the closing document of the Fourth Ibero-American 
Summit just held in Cartagena de Indias. The next summits will 
be held in Argentina in 1995, Chile in 1996, Venezuela in 1997, 
Portugal in 1998, Panama in the year 2,000, and Peru in the year 
2,001. 
  Vice Foreign Minister Jorge Bolanos, who participated in the 
meeting of experts which analyzed the closing document, 
announced Cuba's formal request during a news conference on 
Saturday. 

</TEXT>

