<H3> <TI>   Oil Drilling Enterprise Exceeding Goals </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Oil Drilling Enterprise Exceeding Goals </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL1606152694 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 0900 
GMT 16 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1606152694 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Since January, the Central Region Oil Drilling and 
Extraction enterprise has delivered more than 385,000 tons of 
oil, thus surpassing its projected goals by 3 percent. The 
enterprise director, Engineer Marcos Aguilera, told national 
reporters that the workers' efforts were paired with positive 
results from foreign companies in charge of exploiting several 
wells and the regular arrival of tankers. 
  Engineer Aguilera added that the current situation allows us 
to believe that this overage can be maintained or surpasssed by 
the end of the first semester, at which time they expect to have 
extracted 410,870 tons. 

</TEXT>

