<F P=100> MEXICO </F>
<H3> <TI>   Chiapas </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Chiapas </PHRASE></F></HT>


<TEXT>
Peace   Commissioner Camacho Solis Resigns 

<F P=102> PA1706035394 Madrid EFE in Spanish 0319 GMT 17 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA1706035394 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid EFE </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>
BFN 

  [Text] Mexico City, 16 Jun (EFE) -- Today, Manuel Camacho 
Solis, commissioner for peace and reconciliation in Chiapas, 
resigned his post due to criticisms made by PRI [Institutional 
Revolutionary Party] Candidate Ernesto Zedillo on his role in 
the Chiapas conflict. 
  Camacho expressed his disagreement with Zedillo's position, 
which he said weakened his efforts in the political negotiations 
with the Zapatist National Liberation Army (EZLN). 
  Camacho's resignation is in a letter to Mexican President 
Carlos Salinas de Gortari, which Camacho read to journalists at 
a hotel in Mexico City at 2100 local (0300 GMT Friday). 

</TEXT>

