<H3> <TI>   Further on Resignation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Further on Resignation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA1706041394 Mexico City NOTIMEX in Spanish 0343 GMT 17 Jun 
94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1706041394 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City NOTIMEX </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Mexico City, 16 Jun (NOTIMEX) -- Manuel Camacho 
Solis, commissioner for peace and reconciliation in the 
southeastern Mexican State of Chiapas today announced his 
decision to leave that presidential post and return to private 
life. 
  President Carlos Salinas de Gortari designated Camacho Solis 
peace commissioner on 10 January to seek reconciliation with the 
armed group that emerged in the north-central area of Chiapas on 
1 January to fight for the demands of indigenous groups. 

</TEXT>

