<F P=100> Guatemala </F>
<H3> <TI>   Third Electric Pylon Dynamited </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Third Electric Pylon Dynamited </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA1606180794 Mexico City NOTIMEX in Spanish 1652 GMT 16 Jun 
94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1606180794 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City NOTIMEX </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Guatemala City, 16 Jun (NOTIMEX) -- Official sources 
confirmed today that a group of unidentified people dynamited an 
electricity pylon in the municipality of Concepcion in the 
southern department of Escuintla. As a result, several 
communities have no electricity. 
  The National Police indicated that early this morning 
several 
men planted dynamite cartridges on two of the four sides of the 
pylon, which was partly destroyed while the homes of some 
100,000 people were left without electric power. 
  According to the Police, the Army arrived in the area and 
began to comb the mountains for those responsible for the attack. 
  The Police said that last Saturday another two electricity 
pylons were dynamited in the country's interior, and no victims 
have been reported yet. 
  The attacks took place within the framework of the meeting 
between the government and the Guatemalan guerrillas in Oslo, 
Norway, where the parties are considering the creation of a 
Verification Commission of the Historic Past. Guatemala has 
endured a 34-year armed conflict, which has resulted in some 
175,000 victims. 

</TEXT>

